# Python Pipeline Conventions

## General

- Use type hints on all function signatures
- Active pipeline code: `scripts/feature_engineering/`, `scripts/export/`; legacy standalone filters live in `scripts/_archive/` (Phase 1.0)
- Each script should be runnable standalone with `argparse` (CLI-friendly defaults)
- Use `pathlib.Path` for file paths, not string concatenation

## Data Rules

- Primary key: `id` (TMDB ID); secondary dedup key: `imdb_id`
- Must-drop rows: null genres, zero/null vote_count, zero/null vote_average, null release_date, null overview (with title fallback — see Tech Spec §2)
- Dynamic vote_count threshold: see `scripts/_archive/filter_dynamic_baseline_vote_count.py`
- Temporal jitter for YYYY-01-01 placeholders: deterministic seed = TMDB `id`

## Embedding

- Model A (subsample/debug): `paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2` (384d)
- Model B (full/quality): `paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2` (768d)
- Input: `"Tagline: {tagline}\nOverview: {overview}"` (omit tagline line if empty)
- Truncate to 3000 chars from tail; L2-normalize output

## Feature Fusion (before UMAP)

- Each group (text, genre, lang) independently L2-normalized, then scaled by `1/√d`
- Configurable weights: `w_text`, `w_genre`, `w_lang` (default 1.0 each)

## Dependencies

- Pin major.minor versions in `requirements.cpu.txt` (included by `requirements.txt`); WSL GPU conda spec: `scripts/env/rapids_env.yml`; optional pip-only extras for that env: `requirements.gpu.txt`
- PyTorch: for GPU embeddings, install CUDA wheels from PyTorch’s wheel index (`https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128` or the variant listed on pytorch.org for your OS/driver); PyPI-default `torch` is CPU (`+cpu`). See Tech Spec §2.1.1.
- GPU-first for sentence-transformers encode; lower batch_size on OOM, never drop samples
